describe("createOrUpdatePRComment", () => {
  it("creates a new comment when no bot comment exists", async () => {
    const octokit = createMockOctokit({ existingComments: [] });
    await createOrUpdatePRComment(octokit, "owner", "repo", 42, "## Preview\nReady");
    expect(octokit.issues.createComment).toHaveBeenCalledWith({
      owner: "owner",
      repo: "repo",
      issue_number: 42,
      body: "## Preview\nReady",
    });
  });

  it("updates existing bot comment instead of creating new one", async () => {
    const octokit = createMockOctokit({
      existingComments: [
        { id: 555, body: "<!-- gblockparty-bot -->\n## Old comment" },
      ],
    });
    await createOrUpdatePRComment(octokit, "owner", "repo", 42, "## Preview\nReady");
    expect(octokit.issues.updateComment).toHaveBeenCalledWith({
      owner: "owner",
      repo: "repo",
      comment_id: 555,
      body: "## Preview\nReady",
    });
    expect(octokit.issues.createComment).not.toHaveBeenCalled();
  });

  it("identifies bot comment by marker across paginated results", async () => {
    const octokit = createMockOctokit({
      existingComments: [
        // Page 1: 100 non-bot comments
        ...Array.from({ length: 100 }, (_, i) => ({ id: i, body: "Some comment" })),
        // Page 2: bot comment
        { id: 999, body: "<!-- gblockparty-bot -->\n## Deploy Preview" },
      ],
    });
    await createOrUpdatePRComment(octokit, "owner", "repo", 42, "Updated");
    expect(octokit.issues.updateComment).toHaveBeenCalledWith(
      expect.objectContaining({ comment_id: 999 }),
    );
  });
});
```

### Integration Tests for Webhook Route

```typescript
describe("POST /api/webhooks/github", () => {
  it("returns 401 for invalid signature", async () => {
    const res = await POST(createWebhookRequest("push", {}, "wrong-sig"));
    expect(res.status).toBe(401);
  });

  it("returns 200 for valid push event", async () => {
    const res = await POST(createWebhookRequest("push", validPushPayload, validSignature));
    expect(res.status).toBe(200);
    const data = await res.json();
    expect(data.received).toBe(true);
  });

  it("deduplicates by delivery ID", async () => {
    const req = createWebhookRequest("push", validPushPayload, validSignature, "delivery-123");
    await POST(req);
    const res = await POST(req);
    const data = await res.json();
    expect(data.duplicate).toBe(true);
  });

  it("returns 400 for invalid JSON body", async () => {
    const res = await POST(createWebhookRequest("push", "not json{{{", validSignature));
    expect(res.status).toBe(400);
  });
});
```

---

## Performance Considerations

1. **Webhook response time**: The handler must return 200 within 10 seconds (GitHub's timeout). By processing the webhook asynchronously (fire-and-forget), the response is sent in <10ms.

2. **Deduplication set size**: Capped at 1000 entries. At typical webhook volume (a few per hour), this covers days of deliveries. The eviction is approximate FIFO.

3. **PR comment pagination**: The `findBotComment()` function paginates through all comments. For PRs with hundreds of comments, this could be slow. In practice, the bot comment is usually among the first few comments (added early in the PR's life). Future optimization: search from newest to oldest if this becomes an issue.

4. **No database in the hot path**: The webhook route itself does no database queries. Only the background handler does (for installation tracking). Push and PR handlers currently only log.
